javadoc:
Command to add a label. If the label already
 exists somewhere else, the address is appended to make
 it unique.
@deprecated The need for this class is now unnecessary since duplicate labels are permitted

methods.name: <init>
methods.comment: Constructs a new command for adding a label.

params.name: address
params.comment: address where the label is to be added.

params.name: name
params.comment:
name of the new label. A null name will cause a default label
 be added.

params.name: namespace
params.comment: the namespace of the label. (i.e. the namespace this label is associated with)

methods.javadoc:
Returns the newly created symbol.
@return the newly created symbol
